The Tree

by Father Thyme

Daybreak over the crater. The Tree looms over everything inside.

In a bed in a small stone hut by the south wall a figure stirs.  That person is me. This is my story. I'll tell it in the way I remember and hope you understand. My education in those days left much to be desired.

Home
This be my home. Stone walls, dirt floor, hole in thu wall on thu north side ter git out,  same as everybody else's. I lives here on me own, I be no loner though. I hev a few friends.

I see's me table and me bed.

I looks up ter thu roof. Thu stone walls curve to dome above. That's how thu old folks built em. Sometimes they falls in. Speshly if a branch falls on em. But if there ain't no roof thu branch kills yer sure. Wood roof 'ed be better but folks ain't allowed Wood. Wood is for fixin' thu ship. Wood is Holy stuff. Jake Wilkins  put a Wood strut in his roof years ago. They hung him for sacrilege. Scuse my ramblin'. I allus rambles first thing in thu mornin' on a empty stomick.

I climbs out of thu bed. I hev a proper bone bed, not like some as sleeps on the dirt. I smooths out thu heephide cover and debates whether to have breakfast or go fer a walk fust. Mebbe I'll go ter thu service at thu Ship, thet be Shipsday terday. Or mebbe not. Mebbe I'll go up north an stand on thu Looksee awhile. I likes ter look et the dot an wonder what et be.
> x table

> x table
Thu tabletop is heephide varnished stiff wi glassberry juice. Thu legs is human femurs. Gramps end is a mite higher than Grams. He wus a tall fella.
On it is  splat fruit and me cup.
> x bed

> x bed
Fair comfortable. Rib cages is quite springy. I gets them from thu morgue. Part o' me quota.
> out

> out
I goes out through thu door hole. I looks around, there  be a yaller sky this mornin' cept what's covered by Thu Tree, which is most of et. Thu Tree branches they reach near to the crater wall. That's south. Thu crater wall circle right about thu place. Only place you kin climb thu wall be up north ut thu Looksee. Thu Tree you can't climb a tall. Less you want a broke neck. Plenty tried, plenty died. Bark be smooth like glassberry skin. Tree stand dead centre o' crater. Praise Thu Tree.

Most folks lives scattered in homes near thu crater walls. I ain't distubin' any on a Shipsday. Ter thu east I sees Crusher Bayliss clan sittin' by thu crater wall. They be lowlife soupers. I ain't goin' near, they kill I easy. I see Crusher, he shake fist. He don't like I.

Outside home
South o' here is my home, north is The Tree, Praise The Tree! East there's some other homes but I ain't goin' over there, they is mean folks, they is soupers. Northeast is thu morgue. West is thu heep pens. South east an sou' west be thu crater wall. Thet be too steep fer ter climb.
