> n
SPLAT!

As I walks up to the tree a splat fruit comes down . Two  kids   runs out with blade bones and scoops it up. They runs off afore I kin grab any. Pity.

Beside the Tree
This's Thu Tree. I be stood by thu trunk here. Praise thu Tree.  South o' here is my home. East is thu morgue. North is Looksee.

I see's The Tree.
> x tree

> x tree
The Tree. Praise Thu Tree. Be forty five manspans round thu trunk. We ain't got forty five men now. People is thinned out a mite, we be dyin' out, doubt if there be hunnered left countin' men, wimmin an kids. Thu tree were measured  long times ago. The branches they reach out right te the crater wall. Thets near eight hunnred steps. You can feel the oxy comin' down here. Feels good. The leaves be purple they don't fall cept when a branch fall. Sometimes a small branch o' leaves they die, then thu branch they be on fall. An then the Lieutenant he take it for the ship. Trunk be real smooth, long way ter low branch. Nobody yet find way up.  No need, all we want falls down. We hev branchfalls fer thu ship, splat fruit fer eat an juice. Praise Thu Tree! Pipe stick out from tree, water run out for wash an drink.
> ne

> ne
I come to the ship. I see the Lieutenant. He's standin' by the airlock (he don't hev a hole in the wall, he hev a airlock, it amount ter similar thing). He hev on his long heepskin robe, his shoulder pips o' metal an foot covers he call boots. He shout at I. He say "You naff off punk. There ain't no service today I ain't in no state ter run no singin' o' hymns. I got the flux bad." He turn away a'coffin'. I knows better thun ter go in. He hev the Holy Gun in his hand. He go back in, I ain't follerin' him. He gets plenty het up sometimes speshly when he ain't well. Which 's most times. Personal I thinks he drink too much splat beer. He look a lot worse today n' I seen him afore. He stagger inta airlock still a'coffin'.

Outside the ship
I be standin' by thu ship west be thu Looksee. South be thu morgue.

I see's the ship.
