I feel buzz in ears. I SPLITTING HEAD HURT!  HELP! I can't thi---

I seem to be rising through a fog of confusing memories. My past life seems to have been lived by someone else. I remember it clearly as a time I did not understand as much as I do now. I am finding this very difficult to explain as I am new to all this. I understand that I have been enhanced mentally by an Updater Unit, an educational device keeping the brain at optimum efficiency and installing new knowledge. I know exactly where I am and what has happened.

I am upset that my ancestors did not realise that they could just have picked up branches, walked back to the ship and gone on with their mission.

I remove the headphones. They retract into the side of the seat.
> x dashboard

> x dashboard
The dashboard of the ATV.
On it I see a control port.
> put spike in control port

> put spike in control port
The computer crackles into life and announces in a reedy voice:

THIS VEHICLE HAS NOT BEEN SERVICED FOR 250 YEARS 2 MONTHS AND 5 DAYS. THIS IS CONTRARY TO SAFETY REQUIREMENTS. INDUCTION ACTIVATOR FLUID IS REQUIRED URGENTLY. AN INDUCTION FLUID INPUT ORIFICE IS LOCATED ON THE REAR BULKHEAD.  CARE SHOULD BE TAKEN NOT TO ALLOW  EXCESSIVE  DELAYS BETWEEN  ROUTINE SERVICES IN FUTURE.
> put flask in input orifice

> put flask in input orifice
I pour the full contents of  the flask into the funnel and discard it. Lights begin flashing on the computer.

I move to the computer terminal and sit in the driving seat.

THIS VEHICLE IS NOW FUNCTIONAL BUT IN A BAD MECHANICAL CONDITION.  OPTIMUM ADVICE FROM THIS TERMINAL WOULD BE TO RETURN TO THE SHIP BEFORE FURTHER MALFUNCTIONS OCCUR.

I decide to err on the side of caution. "Affirmative, return to Aries."

The engine splutters, then roars into life. The vehicle begins to turn around, shaking down tons of sand off the upper surfaces. It slowly rumbles clear of the dust cloud it has raised and rumbles off  in a northerly direction, picking up speed as it goes.

Far to the north a small spot appears and quickly takes on the lines of a Zodiac class starship. It can only be the Aries. The ATV rumbles to a halt beside it.

The computer announces:

THIS VEHICLE HAS FULFILLED ITS PRIME OBJECTIVE, HAVING MOVED TO A NON LIFE THREATENING POSITION IN EMERGENCY MODE. REACTIVATION WILL NOT BE POSSIBLE UNTIL A FULL MAINTENANCE PROGRAMME HAS BEEN CARRIED OUT.

I can see a dashboard (on which there is a control port (in which there is a metal spike)) and seats.
The branch seems to have died. I don't think that will be any more use. Luckily I managed to refill a breather unit from the now working oxy dispenser. This one was not taken as it was already empty. I don the breather and get ready to leave.

The ATV is not going anywhere but with the breather unit working I can go outside.
> out

> out
I step out of the ATV cabin. I am impressed by the Aries. I have learned the basic workings of a starship but have never seen one before. I can only be awed at such a marvel of engineering.

