Living Area
This seems to be a general living area with padded chairs, low tables, a large dining table and a bio chef unit (at least that's what it says on the front). Exits are west and south into the passage. Maybe I can use the bio chef. I'm starving.

You can see a Bio Chef unit.
> use bio chef unit

> use bio chef unit
I go and stand in front of the unit. A polite voice speaks out of the unit.

"Your personal preference is not on record. A body scan shows that you are malnourished. Rations have been therefore been provided according to your needs."

A pair of plates rise from the table through a sliding arrangement. A short knife, a four pronged device I forget the name of and a spoon  are also provided. One plate contains a thick piece of roast meat and a brown crispy vegetable cut in strips.  The other a crusted brown triangle containing a whitish fruit, it has a very cold white lump beside it. I don't understand why two plates were used. I pour it all onto the bigger plate.The food tastes strange but delicious. It was definitely not heep.  As I finish eating, the tableware vanishes into the unit. Pity, I should have kept the knife. Perhaps I should have gone to a table, then brought the dirty dishes back. Never mind.

While eating I gave a good part of the meat to the dog. I am not used to such large portions. These spacemen must be fat as grints.
> w

> w

Bathroom
This appears to be a bathroom. A shiny square on the wall must be, according to my educational update, a mirror, the white object a toilet and the large cabinet a shower.

You can see a toilet and a shower.
> use toilet

> use toilet
I decide to use a civilised toilet for the first time in my life. It is a very strange experience. I am fascinated to see my waste washed away by jets of water. It seems strange to throw away good fertiliser, but what would I use it for now? I suspect that it is recycled in some way anyway. As I stand up a disembodied voice orders."NOW SANITISE YOUR HANDS." I am puzzled as to why I should break with the habits of a lifetime.
> use shower

> use shower
I remove my robe and step into the shower. A  door slides round me. A rather invasive blue mist appears, swirls vigorously  into all nooks and crannies, then dissipates leaving me immaculately clean, including my loincloth. I step out and recover my robe. Well! That was an experience.
