> e

> e
I enter the control room of the Aries. Now I know what a starship bridge really looks like! Not a small wooden replica. The room is impressive despite the fact that everything is shut down.

The bridge
The room is dominated by the large control chair in the centre. There are very few controls. Far less than I would have expected. The ship is obviously heavily automated.

You can see a control chair.
> x control chair

> x control chair
The main control chair is an imposing device. There are numerous buttons, none of which work.
> sit on control chair

> sit on control chair
A green light flashes on. A voice announces.

A MEMBER OF THE REGISTERED CREW IS ACKNOWLEDGED. THIS UNIT RECOGNISES THAT A SERIOUS MALFUNCTION HAS OCCURRED. A DISTRESS CALL HAS BEEN SENT.

There is a pause of several minutes, then a haze forms in front of the control chair which slowly forms into a tall kindly looking man sitting at a desk. I know now that this is a holo projection. Ghost indeed!

"GREETINGS!" The man says, "I was amazed to hear that the Aries had contacted us. Do you know we have been searching for a quarter millennium. You are on a par with the Mary Celeste, the Flying Dutchman and the third Venus expedition."

I explain the situation to him and learn that he is Sector Marshal Travis, Admiral of the North Arm (whatever that may mean)  and that we have completely missed the Hundred Years' War against the Vulkit Swarm, the JB40 Pandemic and the the great pulse which wiped out half the human race. He asks for our coordinates.

I am torn. It seems being civilised is a very chancy business. I feel that with the resources of a starship behind us we can turn ourselves round and make a small paradise of this planet, before returning to the human race.

Or perhaps we should reveal our whereabouts and accept a well meaning invasion.

I have made my decision. I shall return, educate people then put it to the vote. I think a few theatricals with a hover suit may well overawe the souper clan.

Wish me luck, farewell. I shall miss your directions.

THE END
